@startuml orchestration-layers
title Orchestration — three layers (introduced 2026-05-18)

skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam BackgroundColor #fafafa
skinparam ArrowColor #000000
skinparam ArrowFontColor #000000
skinparam ArrowFontSize 11
skinparam ArrowThickness 1.3
skinparam nodesep 16
skinparam ranksep 26
hide stereotype

skinparam package {
  FontColor #111
  FontSize 13
  FontStyle bold
  BorderColor #444
  BorderThickness 2
}

skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #1f4768
  FontColor #111
  RoundCorner 8
}

' ============================================================
' Layer 3 — project-local
' ============================================================

package "Layer 3 — project-local (in EVERY consuming repo)" as L3 #f0f0e8 {
  rectangle ".claude/skills/loop/SKILL.md\n(project-local Ralph-loop driver)" as Loop #d6e6f5

  rectangle "knows THIS repo's:\n• queue path resolution\n• dispatch table (item-kind → verb)\n• janitor invocation\n  (just check + /livespec:doctor)\n• budget / mode policy\n• escalation rules\n• commit / PR conventions" as L3Notes #lavender
}

' ============================================================
' Layer 2 — plugin primitives (skills)
' ============================================================

package "Layer 2 — plugin primitives (skills, the contract surface)" as L2 #fde8ec {

  package "livespec-core (8 skills)" as Core #fff5f5 {
    rectangle "heavyweight:\n• seed\n• propose-changes\n• critique\n• revise\n• doctor\n• prune-history\n• help" as CoreHeavy
    rectangle "thin transport:\n• next" as CoreThin #ccddee
  }

  package "livespec-impl-* (9 skills)" as Impl #e3f0e3 {
    rectangle "heavyweight:\n• capture-impl-gaps\n• capture-spec-drift\n• capture-work-item\n• implement\n• capture-memo\n• process-memos" as ImplHeavy
    rectangle "thin transport:\n• list-memos\n• list-work-items\n• next" as ImplThin #ccddee
  }
}

' ============================================================
' Layer 1 — deterministic CLIs
' ============================================================

package "Layer 1 — deterministic CLIs (Python implementations behind every skill)" as L1 #eef4fb {
  rectangle ".claude-plugin/scripts/bin/\n  next.py\n  list-memos.py\n  list-work-items.py\n  doctor.py --json\n  ... (one per skill)" as CLIs
}

' ============================================================
' Edges
' ============================================================

Loop -[#5a3a72]-> CoreThin : reads spec-side\nranking
Loop -[#5a3a72]-> ImplThin : reads impl-side\nranking
Loop -[#5a3a72]-> CoreHeavy : dispatches\n(interactive, spec-side)
Loop -[#5a3a72]-> ImplHeavy : dispatches\n(autonomous,\nimpl-side)

CoreHeavy ..> CLIs : delegates
CoreThin ..> CLIs : delegates
ImplHeavy ..> CLIs : delegates
ImplThin ..> CLIs : delegates

' ============================================================
' Notes
' ============================================================

note bottom of L3 : The loop driver does NOT live in core OR in\nan impl plugin. Both lack the per-repo knowledge\nrequired. It is checked into each consuming repo\nand hand-tuned. The copier template at\nlivespec-core/templates/impl-plugin/ ships a\nstarter; CI's copier-drift check excludes this\nfile (local divergence is expected).

note right of L2 : The Layer 2 contract is uniform across impl\nplugins. Heavyweight skills carry authored\ndialogue/detection logic. Thin-transport skills\nare deterministic pass-throughs to Layer 1\nCLIs (short SKILL.md, no logic accretion).\nMode discipline: --mode interactive default for\nspec-side dispatch (human-gated); --mode\nautonomous default for impl-side dispatch\n(hands-off the user wants).

note right of L1 : Layer 1 is testable directly (pytest against\nthe Python implementations). Non-Claude consumers\n(CI scripts, just targets) can invoke CLIs\ndirectly. But the contract surface is the Layer 2\nskill; the CLI is plumbing. Within a Claude Code\nsession, the Layer 3 loop invokes skills (not\nCLIs) so the dispatch is namespace-aware and\nClaude Code's plugin model handles it natively.

@enduml
